        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36318",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, the Abstract action helper does not define a constructor at all; if you want to do initialization tasks in helpers, the time to do it is in the constructor. I've removed the init() method at this point as it is uncalled from anywhere, and was simply confusing the issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T10:13:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T10:13:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36339",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=est",
                        "name": "est",
                        "displayName": "Ernest Szulikowski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This patch destroyed my project ;)\r\n\r\nThrows fatal error: \r\n{noformat}Fatal error: Call to undefined method IPMCore_Controller_Action_Helpers_NavigationLoader::init() in D:\\www\\SvnIPMCore\\ipmcore\\lib\\zendf\\zend\\Zend\\Controller\\Action\\HelperBroker.php on line 253{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=est",
                        "name": "est",
                        "displayName": "Ernest Szulikowski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T11:47:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T11:47:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36341",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aheimlich",
                        "name": "aheimlich",
                        "displayName": "Aaron Heimlich",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Matthew,\r\n\r\nUnless I'm misunderstanding something, the {{init()}} you just removed actually _is_ called from several places in {{Zend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker}}. Namely:\r\n\r\n# In {{Zend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker::__construct()}} on line 253\r\n# In {{Zend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker::getHelper()}} on line 307",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aheimlich",
                        "name": "aheimlich",
                        "displayName": "Aaron Heimlich",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T11:55:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T11:55:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36344",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=est",
                        "name": "est",
                        "displayName": "Ernest Szulikowski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am adding my helper in Bootstrap this way: \r\n{noformat}\r\nZend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker::addHelper(\r\n            new IPMCore_Controller_Action_Helpers_NavigationLoader());\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=est",
                        "name": "est",
                        "displayName": "Ernest Szulikowski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T11:59:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T11:59:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36366",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "init() is called in several locations, but not from getStaticHelper(). Re-opening.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T14:07:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T14:07:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36368",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm reinstating the init() method as it _was_ in use. However, this request will not be honored.\r\n\r\ninit() in the action helpers is called when the broker is instantiated -- at which time, the action controller is available and injected into each action helper currently registered with the broker. As such, it is intended to allow you to setup a clean object state for the new action controller and\/or perform actions that require knowledge of the action controller -- not perform constructor initialization tasks. If you need tasks done at construction time, do them in the constructor, or call init() from your constructor.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-20T14:18:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-20T14:18:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36448",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=brunitto",
                        "name": "brunitto",
                        "displayName": "Bruno Piraj\u00e1 Moyle",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Although the request will not be honored, I think it will be nice to add a note in the reference guide, specifying that construction time tasks should be defined in custom constructor or init() methods.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=brunitto",
                        "name": "brunitto",
                        "displayName": "Bruno Piraj\u00e1 Moyle",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-23T16:38:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-23T16:38:48.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
